  Thomas P. Caruso, Ph.D., MBA, PMP is the technical project manager for CCFA Partners, and health informatics liaison research associate in the School of Information and Library Science at UNC Chapel Hill.  Dr. Caruso has been developing clinical research information systems for six years, most recently managing Clinical Trial Database (CTDB) support by a team at NIH for Technical Frontiers, Inc.  In partnership with RTI, Dr. Caruso has also built a Self-Generated Health Information Exchange (SGHIx) to allow individuals to aggregate, analyze and share their personal health data.  In addition he has Project Management Professional certification.